commentTextItems.html: short of a length, hit on the rise, a few bounces and over the ropes. India win!

commentPostTextItems.html: Comfortable win for India. Sachin Tendulkar 122 not out takes the honours. India and West Indies will meet in the final for the Coca Cola Cup on Saturday, 07 July 2001.
We will be back with you with all the live action on the 7th July at 0700 GMT.
Kindly send in your comments/opinions to comms@cricinfo.com
Thanks for being with us. So long.

commentTextItems.html: outside the leg stump, played square of the wicket on th eleg side

commentPostTextItems.html: India need four runs to win, two overs remain

commentTextItems.html: played to mid-wicket

commentTextItems.html: on the pads, picked up and played in the air, down tolong leg for four

drives it firmly back to the bowler

stories.title: The curious case of a player being punished for an umpire's mistake
stories.summary:
The 29th over of the Indian reply chasing a West Indian total of 230
in the Coca Cola Cup triangular series game at Harare on Wednesday
sparked off a rather strange controversy

stories.title: Windies wicket-keeper Jacobs banned
stories.summary: West Indian wicket-keeper Ridley Jacobs has been suspended for the three One Day Internationals versus Kenya, being 15, 16 and 19 August 2001, as a result of an incident during the One Day International Match held on 4 July, in Harare, Zimbabwe,

stories.title: 6th Match, India v West Indies, Coca Cola Cup, Statistical Highlights
stories.summary: It was the 1733rd ODI in cricket history

stories.title: Tendulkar's 29th century hands India a comfortable victory
stories.summary:
This last match of the first round of the triangular tournament was
meaningless as far as the competition was concerned, as both teams had
already qualified at the expense of Zimbabwe
